Section 1:
HB 3500 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version House Bill 3500 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted WEST virginia legislature2025 regular sessionIntroducedHouse Bill 3500By Delegate Hornbuckle [Introduced March 18, 2025; referred to the Committee on Education]A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new section, designated §18C-1-4a, relating to creating the "Governor's Cup Challenge" to provide scholarships for high school student-athletes who participated in high school athletic extracurricular activities but did not receive an athletic scholarship to an in-state institution of higher education, and who are pursuing an education at the institution.Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia: Article 18C. STUDENT LOANS; SCHOLARSHIPS AND STATE AID. §18C-1-4a. Governor's Cup Challenge. (a) The "Governor's Cup Challenge" is hereby created to provide scholarships for high school student-athletes who participated in high school athletic extracurricular activities but did not receive an athletic scholarship to an in-state institution of higher education, and who are pursuing an education at the institution.(b) The Governor's Cup Challenge shall consist of athletic contests between Marshall University and West Virginia University in athletic program in which both colleges compete in within Division 1, NCAA competition. These contests shall be played on an annual basis. The location of the athletic contests shall be agreed upon by both institutions and included as part of the athletic team's regular athletic calendar. The location of each athletic contest shall rotate annually between the two institutions and may also be hosted at other locations around the state upon agreement by both institutions. (c) Each athletic contest won will earn one point for the winning institution. The institution with the most points at the end of the year shall be named the winner of the Governor's Cup Challenge.(d) Twenty percent of the total net profits from ticket sales, merchandise sales, concession sales, and other game-related revenue shall be deposited at least annually by each institution into the "West Virginia Athlete Scholarship Fund" which is hereby created. The annual Governor's Cup Challenge champion will annually receive 65 percent of the balance of the fund to use for scholarships at their institution for in-state high school athletes. The other institution shall annually receive 35 percent of the fund for scholarships at their institution for in-state high school athletes. (e) The Governor's Cup Challenge and the West Virginia Athlete Scholarship Fund shall be overseen and monitored by the vice chancellor for administration as provided for in §18C-1-1 of this code.   NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to establish the "Governor's Cup Challenge" to provide scholarships for high school student-athletes who did not receive an athletic scholarship to a West Virginia higher education institution and are perusing an education at their preferred in-state institution of higher education. Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law, and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


